President Donald J. Trump shared his vision for the American economy at the World Economic Forum in Davos. He emphasized that America is open for business and that he will always put America first. The economy has seen growth due to measures such as tax cuts, deregulation, pro-growth energy policies, and stronger trade practices. As a result, over 255 companies have announced new benefits for their workers, including bonuses, higher wages, and better retirement options. President Trump has taken his America First vision to various parts of the world, and if the participants at the forum work together, it could lead to positive change.